          <section id="contrib-structure" class="docs-section">
            <h3>Repo Structure</h3>
            <pre class="docs-pre"><code>opencourses/
├── engine/                  ← course engine (Bun/TypeScript)
│   ├── courses/             ← course directories (one per course)
│   ├── lib/                 ← shared utilities (github.ts, parse-course.ts)
│   ├── scripts/             ← all runnable scripts (one per workflow job)
│   ├── types/               ← TypeScript interfaces (course.ts)
│   ├── sandbox/             ← Docker sandbox for code grading
│   └── package.json
├── site/                    ← Astro static site
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── components/      ← Astro components
│   │   ├── data/            ← JSON data files + oc.ts
│   │   ├── layouts/         ← Base.astro layout
│   │   └── pages/           ← one .astro file per route
│   ├── public/              ← static assets
│   └── astro.config.mjs
├── .github/
│   ├── workflows/           ← GitHub Actions (10 workflows)
│   └── ISSUE_TEMPLATE/      ← enrollment-request, quiz-submit, project-submit
└── package.json             ← Bun workspace root</code></pre>
          </section>

          <section id="contrib-engine" class="docs-section">
            <h3>Engine Internals</h3>
            <p><strong>Key libraries:</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li><code>engine/lib/github.ts</code> — <code>makeOctokit()</code> (Octokit instance from <code>GITHUB_TOKEN</code>) and <code>repoFromEnv()</code> (parses <code>REPO=owner/repo</code>)</li>
              <li><code>engine/lib/parse-course.ts</code> — <code>parseCourse(path)</code>: reads a <code>course.md</code>, splits YAML frontmatter from Markdown body, validates required fields, returns typed <code>Course</code> object</li>
              <li><code>engine/types/course.ts</code> — all TypeScript interfaces: <code>Course</code>, <code>Chapter</code>, <code>Lesson</code>, <code>Question</code>, <code>ChapterTest</code>, <code>Project</code>, <code>Certificate</code>, <code>LeaderboardEntry</code></li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Script conventions:</strong></p>
            <ul>
              <li>Every script is a standalone <code>#!/usr/bin/env bun</code> file</li>
              <li>Configuration via environment variables (<code>GITHUB_TOKEN</code>, <code>REPO</code>, issue-specific vars)</li>
              <li>Exit code 1 on any unrecoverable error</li>
              <li>All GitHub mutations go through <code>lib/github.ts</code> helpers</li>
              <li>No AI, no external paid APIs — all grading is algorithmic</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section id="contrib-site" class="docs-section">
            <h3>Site Internals</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Framework:</strong> Astro 4, output: static. Zero client-side JS by default.</li>
              <li><strong>Styling:</strong> Custom CSS with design tokens (variables in <code>:root</code>). No Tailwind, no component library.</li>
              <li><strong>Data layer:</strong> <code>site/src/data/oc.ts</code> imports 5 JSON files and exports a typed <code>OC</code> object consumed by all pages.</li>
              <li><strong>Interactive components:</strong> Use <code>&lt;script is:inline&gt;</code> or <code>define:vars</code> for the small amount of JS needed (command palette, theme toggle, TrackMap hover).</li>
              <li><strong>Layout:</strong> All pages use <code>../layouts/Base.astro</code> which includes Navbar, Footer, CommandPalette, and global styles.</li>
              <li><strong>New page pattern:</strong>
                <pre class="docs-pre"><code>---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---
&lt;Base title="Page Title" description="..."&gt;
  &lt;div class="container"&gt;
    &lt;div class="page-head"&gt;
      &lt;!-- breadcrumbs, h1, subtitle --&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;!-- content --&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/Base&gt;</code></pre>
              </li>
            </ul>
