          <section id="arch-sandbox" class="docs-section">
            <h3>Docker Sandbox</h3>
            <p>Code submissions run in <code>engine/sandbox/</code> — a Docker image with strict resource limits:</p>
            <pre class="docs-pre"><code>docker run \
  --network none          # no internet access
  --memory 256m           # 256 MB RAM limit
  --cpus 1                # single CPU
  --read-only             # filesystem is read-only
  --tmpfs /tmp:size=100m  # 100 MB writable temp
  --user 1001:1001        # non-root user
  --security-opt no-new-privileges</code></pre>
            <p>The sandbox receives student code and test inputs via environment variables and mounts. It outputs <code>/tmp/test-results.json</code>:</p>
            <pre class="docs-pre"><code>&#123;"passed": true, "score": 9, "maxScore": 10, "tests": [
  &#123;"input": "[3,1]", "expected": "[1,3]", "actual": "[1,3]", "passed": true&#125;,
  ...
]&#125;</code></pre>
            <p>Supported languages and their executors: Python 3 (<code>python3</code>), JavaScript (<code>node</code>), Bash (<code>bash</code>), Java (<code>javac</code> + <code>java</code>), Go (<code>go run</code>), Rust (<code>rustc</code>), C (<code>gcc</code>), C++ (<code>g++</code>).</p>
          </section>

          <section id="arch-certs" class="docs-section">
            <h3>Certificate Format</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Format:</strong> SVG with embedded Open Badges 3.0 metadata (<code>&lt;metadata&gt;</code> element)</li>
              <li><strong>Signed:</strong> GPG-signed using the project's signing key (<code>GPG_SIGNING_KEY</code> secret)</li>
              <li><strong>Published:</strong> GitHub Release asset on the main repo, tagged <code>cert-&#123;student&#125;-&#123;course&#125;-&#123;date&#125;</code></li>
              <li><strong>Verification:</strong> Anyone can verify the GPG signature with the project's public key</li>
              <li><strong>Compliance:</strong> Open Badges 3.0 — includes <code>issuer</code>, <code>recipient</code>, <code>criteria</code>, <code>evidence</code>, <code>issuedOn</code></li>
            </ul>
          </section>

